entry.title: Special Weather Statement issued May 09 at 11:19AM AKDT by NWS
entry.summary: ...RESUSPENDED ASH FROM KATMAI-NOVARUPTA TONIGHT THROUGH TUESDAY... Strong northwesterly winds gusting up to 45 mph across the Alaska Peninsula may cause resuspended ash tonight through Tuesday created from the 1912 Katmai eruption. The ash will be transported across Shelikof Strait to Kodiak Island. These gusty winds could help mix some of this ash down to near the surface.
